misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that the input 'N' (number of students) will always be at least 1, and does not account for the case where N might be 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: The student fails to consider the boundary condition of an empty data set. In Java, accessing index n-1 when n=0 results in -1, which triggers an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException.

misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that a student's name is always a single word and can be captured entirely using Scanner.next().
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: The student does not distinguish between a single token and a full line of text. In Java, Scanner.next() only reads up to the first whitespace, whereas names frequently contain spaces (e.g., 'Alice Smith') which would require Scanner.nextLine().
